title: For Sale:  AR 15-5.56/.223 -Not Cheap, 1 of a Kind
postcontent: This isn't an inexpensive rifle-there are plenty on the market now, so if money is your primary concern, don't look any further. Why is this one of a kind? It was not built to sell or for a showpiece.People often refer to their gun as "rare" to get your attention or justify a high price. This rifle starts with a Palmetto receiver sn SC000XXX. If you're familiar with Palmetto you recognize that's not a normal SN. The SC denoted South Carolina and the manufacturer of the receiver-FN.This is one of 500 made by FN for Palmetto while FN was only building for the military, and prior to them entering the commercial market.The barrel is a Black Hole Weaponry 16 inch 1-8 twist polygonal barrel, mid length, stainless steel, pencil configuration. Polygonal barrels are noted as the most accurate, durable, and easily cleaned type. Additionally the rifle uses an M16 stainless steel hd bolt carrier group,Midwest Industries 15 inch free float FDE SS series Gen2 handguard, Ergo F93 8 position FDE stock and buffer tube assy.,ALG fire control group, Vltor BCM charging handle and is topped with a Nikon P223 BDC scope and mount.Included are 14 magazines (Magpul and Thermold) 20 & 30 round capacity, and approximately 700 rounds factory .223 ammo.This is the last of 3 rifles built and has been test fired, but not sighted in.The other 2 rifles were extremely accurate out to 300 yards and capable of placing 40 rounds (2-20 rd mags) into a 2 inch diameter hole at 35 yards using a Vortex strikefire red dot sight.Not looking for trades-emptying safe, only reason this is for sale.Must pick up in Moody, AL drivers license or pistol permit, and sign bill of sale. Serious Inquiries only.
